You are here: SALESFORCE HELP DOCS SERVICE CLOUD Message with Customers in the Service Console

Interact with customers over WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, Apple Messages for Business, SMS, and Messaging for In-App and Web channels.

REQUIRED EDITIONS Available in: Lightning Experience. View required editions

Open Messaging 
Access Messaging through the Service Console app that your admin set up. Log into Omni-Channel to start chatting with customers.

Accept a Message and Chat with a Customer 
When a new message arrives in Messaging, it appears in the Omni-Channel utility or sidebar.

Start a Messaging Session with a Customer 
Proactively start messaging sessions with customers in Service Cloud by sending them a message. Agent-initiated outbound messaging is available in all Messaging channels except Messaging for Web.

Send Images and Files in Messaging Sessions 
Sometimes, only a picture will do. Resolve customer inquiries faster by sending images and files during Service Cloud messaging sessions.

Send Links in Messaging Sessions 
To share a link with a customer in a messaging session, send an enhanced link messaging component, which includes a link title, URL, and image.

Send Voice Messages in Messaging Sessions 
If a customer is more comfortable with spoken instruction, honor their preference. Record and send voice messages up to 1 minute long in enhanced Messaging channels.

Send Messaging Components in Messaging Sessions 
Messaging components let you send structured content, such as a question with clickable options, to customers in enhanced Messaging channels and Messaging for In-App and Web.

Transfer a Messaging Session 
Increase your capacity to accept incoming messaging sessions by transferring an existing messaging session.

Inactivate a Messaging Session 
When an unresolved conversation has gone idle for a certain period of time, mark it Inactive so that you can accept an incoming messaging session.

End a Messaging Session 
When youâ€™re done helping a customer, end the messaging session from the conversation window or from the Messaging Sessions list view.

Messaging Error Codes 
Identify errors encountered during WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, Apple Messages for Business, and SMS messaging sessions.
